<a href="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/jump?iu=/8900/24.com/Web/DailySun/News/National_Article&sz=300x250&c=1727757231&t=artid%3dfdf88f9f-4505-4fb0-b8a0-1fcbb7af5c53%26accreditation%3ddaily+sun%26posno%3d2" target="_blank"><img src="http://pubads.g.doubleclick.net/gampad/ad?iu=/8900/24.com/Web/DailySun/News/National_Article&sz=300x250&c=1727757231&t=artid%3dfdf88f9f-4505-4fb0-b8a0-1fcbb7af5c53%26accreditation%3ddaily+sun%26posno%3d2" border="0" alt=""></a>The popular TV pastor, whose main church is in Evaton in the Vaal, south of Joburg, said all proceeds from the dinner will be used to build a community centre.Zondo said a golf tournament had also been planned to raise funds.In 30 years, the church has grown to a membership of more than 20 000 people spread over more than 40 branches across Mzansi.“The ministry will build a community centre that will accommodate 1 200 people,” said Zondo.The primary purpose of the centre, beyond the spiritual objective, will be to host major events to boost tourism in Sedibeng, south of Joburg.It is expected that the planned facility will also create employment opportunities in construction and the hospitality sector.“The estimated cost of the centre is about R100 million but that’s without factoring in possible extra costs. “The ministry has already acquired an 8,5 hectare site in Unitas Park, Vereeniging, in its name,” said Zondo.The church has roped in one of its loyal members and former ANC Sedibeng secretary, Bob Mthembu, to help manage the massive project.In the next few months, Zondo will lead a number of fund-raising activities at the church to raise the cash for the community centre.The cost of the gala dinner, which includes participation in the golf tournament, starts at R2 500 a seat.But those wishing to share the archbishop’s table will have to pay R10 000 a seat.
